&#8220;Covers technology, resources, policy, modelling, futurology, economics, politics, generation technologies, energy conservation, renewables, combined heat and power (CHP), transmission grids, nuclear, and solar. Climate change and peak oil are taken as givens.
Members share, swap and/or sell information, technology, jobs, ideas, policies, etc, with an underlying view that we are headed for difficult times on the Energy Front. There is no group policy as such – merely an ongoing debate.
Some members are highly placed, running large base-load power stations at executive level, others are involved in the upper levels of energy utilities, e.g. National Grid, Centrica, Civil Service and other National Transmission systems. Also academics at Professorial level, engineers, managers, consultants, biologist, economists, architects &#8211; reflecting a wide range of expertise and knowledge.&#8221;
